  <description type="morphology">Stems  4--6 mm diam.; scales blackish, linear-lanceolate.  Leaves  erect or arching.  Petiole  black, 1/4--1/3 length of blade, hairs short, mostly simple, multicellular; scales deltate to linear, base broadly hastate-lacerate.  Blade  narrowly ovate, 20--70 Ã— 5--11 cm; base narrowly truncate; apex acute.  Segments  narrowly ovate to linear, 3--5 mm wide; segments at base of blade abruptly reduced, usually reflexed.  Veins  1--2-forked.  Sori  round or oval, sporangia with 32 spores.  n  = 2 n  = 111, apogamous.</description>
